var TRAD_PATHS = [
  "POSITIVIST PATHWAY: Start with an observable puzzle. Derive a testable hypothesis from theory (deductive). Choose a method that allows causal inference (statistical analysis, structured comparison, process tracing). Select cases based on variation in key variables (MSSD, crucial case). Evaluate using empirical evidence and counterfactuals. THE KKV STANDARD: Maximise observable implications of your hypothesis. Avoid selection on the dependent variable. Seek leverage through controlled comparison. Report uncertainty honestly. Key texts: King, Keohane and Verba (1994); Van Evera (1997); Kellstedt and Whitten (2018).",
  "INTERPRETIVIST PATHWAY: Start with a puzzling social practice, contested meaning, or identity formation. Approach with openness to how actors construct their world (abductive/inductive). Choose a method that uncovers meaning (discourse analysis, ethnography, interpretive process tracing). Select cases based on richness of meaning-making, not statistical representativeness. Evaluate through trustworthiness, reflexivity, thick description, and inter-subjective plausibility. BEYOND KKV: Schwartz-Shea and Yanow (2012) argue that interpretive research has its own standards of rigour - not less rigorous than positivism, but differently rigorous. Key texts: Schwartz-Shea and Yanow (2012); Pouliot (2010); Wedeen (2002).",
